"signal_description": "The SIGNAL query is selecting and renaming several columns from the 'defaultview-225' table. The columns selected are 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Number', 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Name', 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Country', 'Inv. Company Code Text', 'Last PO Id', 'Inv. Document Type Text', 'Last PO Purchasing Group', 'Last PO Type', 'Last PO Item Material Group', and 'Last PO Item Plant Name'. If the 'Last PO Id' is null, it is labeled as 'Non-PO Invoice', otherwise it is labeled as 'PO Invoice'. The query also counts the number of case_id's and sums the 'Inv. Converted USD Amount', renaming these as 'No. Invoices' and 'Invoiced Value in $' respectively. The query then calculates the 'Early Payment Rate' by counting the number of case_id's where the difference between 'Last Inv. Item Due Date' and 'Last Inv. Item Clearing Date' is greater than 5 days and either 'Last Inv. Item Cash Discount Percentage1' or 'Last Inv. Item Cash Discount Percentage2' is 0 or null, divided by the total number of case_id's where 'Last Inv. Item Clearing Date' is not null and either 'Last Inv. Item Cash Discount Percentage1' or 'Last Inv. Item Cash Discount Percentage2' is 0 or null, multiplied by 100. The query also counts the number of 'No. Paid Early Invoices' and sums the 'Invoice Amount Paid Early in $' under the same conditions. The results are grouped by the first 10 selected columns and ordered by the 12th column in descending order."
